The paper discusses the development of Relational Forward Models (RFM) for multi-agent learning, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks to make accurate predictions of agents' future behavior in multi-agent environments is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper focuses on the behavior of multiple agents in a shared environment, which is a topic that falls under multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the social interactions between agents, which suggests that it could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the development of artificial agents that can coordinate with one another and with humans in shared environments, which suggests that it could also be categorized under robotics (cs.RO).
